<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900514-0039</DOCNO><DOCID>900514-0039.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Matra S.A.:   Company, Two Other Firms   Plan To Develop Missile</HL><DATE>05/14/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7A</SO><CO>   F.MAT EUROP F.ASP G.MES</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   French defense and electronics company Matra S.A. said itwould join French government-owned Aerospatiale S.A. and WestGermany's Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm G.m.b.H in a project todevelop an improved version of the Roland short-rangesurface-to-air missile.   A linkup among the three companies had been expected sinceThomson S.A. of France and British Aerospace PLC announcedplans late last year for a joint venture to develop missiles.Aerospatiale Chairman Henri Matre indicated then that hewould welcome an alliance with Matra and MBB.</LP><TEXT>   The new missile to be produced by the three companies, theRoland Mach 5, will cost about one billion francs ($181million) to develop over five years, Matra said. Each companywill contribute an equal share to the venture, while overalltechnical coordination will be in the hands of Aerospatiale.</TEXT></DOC>